01/10/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Prosecutors pressed charges Thursday (September 30th) against a former Bosnian Muslim army officer for war crimes committed during the 1992-1995 conflict.
Eso Macic allegedly took part in the torture and killing of Serbian civilians and prisoners of war in 1992 and 1993 in Konic municipality.
(RTRS, BHRT, Radio Free Europe - 30/09/10)
